The President of the United States, Donald Trump, presented the Congressional Medal of Honor to Master Sergeant Matthew Williams in a ceremony held in the East Room. Williams, a Green Beret, was recognized for his heroism during a mission in Afghanistan in 2008. The President commended Williams for his bravery and thanked him for his service. Several previous recipients of the Medal of Honor were also present at the ceremony. Williams' family, including his wife and parents, were in attendance as well. The President emphasized the strength and skill of the United States Army Special Forces and praised their ability to overcome challenges. Williams, who continues to serve in the military, received the highest military distinction in recognition of his courage and dedication to the nation.